      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental boundary conditions must be documented and replicated in the simulation within stated uncertainty bounds at Gradation 2.",
      "rationale": "FDA benchmark experimental conditions (flow rate, rotational speed, fluid viscosity, hematocrit) are fully documented in Hariharan et al. (2011). Simulation boundary conditions match within 1% of nominal values. Measurement uncertainties are propagated into simulation inputs. Gradation 2 satisfied."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., E% or validation uncertainty) must be computed for primary QoI at Gradation 2.",
      "rationale": "Normalized index of hemolysis predictions are compared against five experimental operating points. Mean absolute percentage error is 8.3%; validation uncertainty Uval = 12.1% at 95% confidence. Both metrics are within MRL-2 acceptance thresholds. Gradation 2 achieved."
