      "acceptanceCriteria": "The QoIs used in validation must be directly relevant to the clinical decision (identifying worst-case hemolysis) at Gradation 2.",
      "rationale": "The primary QoI — normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) — is the standard metric used in FDA guidance for blood-contacting device evaluation. Secondary QoIs (shear stress distribution, exposure time) are mechanistically linked to the hemolysis prediction model. Gradation 2 satisfied."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
